    "rationale": "<p>The correct answer is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5\"><mn>5</mn></math>. The given quadratic equation can be rewritten in factored form as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis x minus 8 right parenthesis left parenthesis x plus 3 right parenthesis equals 0\"><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. Based on the zero product property, it follows that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x minus 8 equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x plus 3 equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. Adding&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8\"><mn>8</mn></math> to both sides of the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x minus 8 equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> yields&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 8\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math>. Subtracting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3\"><mn>3</mn></math> from both sides of the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x plus 3 equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> yields&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals negative 3\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>. Therefore, the solutions to the given equation are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8\"><mn>8</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"negative 3\"><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>. It follows that the sum of the solutions to the given equation is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8 plus left parenthesis negative 3 right parenthesis\"><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5\"><mn>5</mn></math>.</p>",
